<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 15 at 4:35AM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTIOUS TRAVEL IS ADVISED FOR THE POTENTIAL OF SLIPPERY
ROADWAYS THIS MORNING...
WEATHER...
* Patchy freezing drizzle will be possible across the Saginaw
Valley and northern Thumb this morning.
* Air temperatures will range between 31 and 33 degrees.
IMPACTS...
* Light icing may lead to slippery roads particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Patchy freezing drizzle means areal coverage or duration of
the freezing drizzle will be limited. Motorists are urged to
use caution and account for variable driving conditions by
slowing down and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
